Prognostic value of two putative sperm function tests: hypo-osmotic swelling and 
bovine sperm mucus penetration test (Penetrak).

Barratt CL(1), McLeod ID, Dunphy BC, Cooke ID.

Author information:
(1)University Department of Obstetrics and Gynaecology, Jessop Hospital for 
Women, Sheffield, UK.

The clinical value of two inexpensive and easy to perform sperm function tests 
(hypo-osmotic swelling and bovine sperm mucus penetration tests) were examined 
in a prospective study of in-vivo conception rates in 325 couples. Both tests 
were of no significant value alone or in combination with traditional semen 
