416. Langenbecks Arch Chir Suppl Kongressbd. 1992:274-7.

[Indications, choice of procedure and results of conservative therapy of spinal 
injuries].

[Article in German]

Hierholzer G(1), Ludolph E.

Author information:
(1)Berufsgenossenschaftliche Unfallklinik Duisburg-Buchholz.

For conservative treatment of injuries of the cervical spine, two different 
methods are available: The HALO fixator and the collar. The choice depends on 
the kind and extension of the injury. Stable thoracic and lumbar vertebral 
fractures are treated in a conservative functional way in order to strengthen 
the muscular apparatus. Three-point-fixation with a brace is not necessary. 
Functional therapeutic methods can also be applied in the case of instable 
fractures if they are not operable. During a rigid confinement to bed, the 
postural reduction by increasing lordosis has turned out to be the treatment of 
choice. As an essential measure the patient has to take part in a "backschool" 
with postural exercises for the daily life.

